(nICacheTLBWays, nDCacheTLBWays).explanation: These are independent architectural configuration parameters that do not causally influence each other as they serve different cache subsystems;

(nICacheTLBWays, DCacheMiss).explanation: The instruction cache TLB configuration does not directly influence data cache miss behavior as they operate on different memory access patterns;

(nICacheTLBWays, nDCacheMSHRs).explanation: These are independent architectural parameters where instruction TLB associativity does not affect the number of data cache miss status holding registers;
